HEADWORD: Lowlily
<hw>Low"li*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a lowly place or manner;
humbly.</def> <mark>[Obs. or R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thinking <qex>lowlily</qex> of himself and highly of those better
than himself.</q> <rj><qau>J. C. Shairp.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lowliness</ent>⟦br⟧
